{"title":"Burning the Old Year","author":{"name":"Naomi Shihab Nye"},"publishDate":"2013-01-07","lines":[{"line":"Letters swallow themselves in seconds.","stanza":1,"number":1},{"line":"Notes friends tied to the doorknob,","stanza":1,"number":2},{"line":"transparent scarlet paper,","stanza":1,"number":3},{"line":"sizzle like moth wings,","stanza":1,"number":4},{"line":"marry the air.","stanza":1,"number":5},{"line":"So much of any year is flammable,","stanza":2,"number":6},{"line":"lists of vegetables, partial poems.","stanza":2,"number":7},{"line":"Orange swirling flame of days,","stanza":2,"number":8},{"line":"so little is a stone.","stanza":2,"number":9},{"line":"Where there was something and suddenly isn’t,","stanza":3,"number":10},{"line":"an absence shouts, celebrates, leaves a space.","stanza":3,"number":11},{"line":"I begin again with the smallest numbers.","stanza":3,"number":12},{"line":"Quick dance, shuffle of losses and leaves,","stanza":4,"number":13},{"line":"only the things I didn’t do","stanza":4,"number":14},{"line":"crackle after the blazing dies.","stanza":4,"number":15}]}